      "date": "2012-08-04 07:48:48.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\nI'm wondering what will happen here if a 1.8 system is upgraded to 2.4 and DNE is enabled?  Will we get conflicting MDT OSC names because there is no \"-MDT0001\" suffix being used?\n\nShould the suffix being ignored be conditional on only \"-MDT0000\"?  I guess that could be fixed as part of the DNE code.",
